Nutrition 21 Supplement Maker Files Bankruptcy with $122.8 Million in Debt

-- B y   T i f f a n y   K a r y
-- 
2011-08-26T20:00:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/nutrition-21-supplement-maker-files-bankruptcy-with-122-8-million-in-debt.html
Nutrition 21 Inc. (NXXI) , a developer of
pharmaceutical type supplements, filed for bankruptcy in  White
Plains , New York.  The Chapter 11 petition today listed $122.8 million in
liabilities and less than $7.2 million in assets. Subsidiaries
Heart’s Content Inc., Iceland Health LLC and Nutrition 21 LLC
also filed. The Purchase, New York-based company’s products
include Chromax chromium picolinate and Zinmax zinc picolinate,
according to its website.  Revenue comes from sale of patented ingredients to vitamin
and supplement makers, for human and animal nutrition, according
to the company’s website.  The case is In re Nutrition 21 LLC, 11-23712, Southern
District of New York (Manhattan).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tiffany Kary in New York at 
 tkary@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Hytha at   mhytha@bloomberg.net . 